#Her30DaysofGratitude | Day 3

My name is Dadé and my deepest gratitude comes from the fact that I’m not perfect.

I make tons of mistakes, I fail more often than not. I didn’t always know this, because I used to validate myself by thinking I was always right. And so many losses later, here I am.

Which leads me to give my whole heart and mind to the love of God. The love that tells me to get up and keep going—the love that allows me to be me in the safest way possible while erasing the burden of ever trying to impress anyone.

It’s teaching me to see the best in others so I can attempt to love them the same—I can’t imagine a more perfect gift.

Thank you Queen @regalwrench for being a part of our gratitude challenge. We love and appreciate you!💛
